The paper deals with fairness in machine learning, specifically in the context of sequential predictions and overlapping populations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses game-theoretic interpretations of their results, which suggests that it may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computational methods to achieve fairness, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the statistical impossibility of achieving fairness in certain cases, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
